lock(mMutex)\".\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22877", "files": ["dom/media/webrtc/MediaEngineTabVideoSource.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9294eb30e6daf90370ec4ca6dacbf6c0f89d0861", "parents": ["2883b91c8f6f0fe8ecfc762787d0ebdb06beef75"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julien Cristau \u003cjcristau@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532554 - point directly at beta release notes from beta builds r=glandium\n\nInstead of relying on a server-side redirect from XX.0 to XX.0beta,\nchange the URL to be the right one for beta and developer edition\nbuilds, like fennec already does in mobile/android/app/mobile.js.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22065", "files": ["browser/branding/aurora/pref/firefox-branding.js", "browser/branding/official/pref/firefox-branding.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b9a333944346bbc04cde322a462ed388a739ad93", "parents": ["9294eb30e6daf90370ec4ca6dacbf6c0f89d0861"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriele Svelto \u003cgsvelto@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533698 - Enable tab unloading in low-memory scenarios on beta too r=mconley\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22680", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b1c9e8f9dab7d6e12b4867f7f7245b5e52b33abf", "parents": ["b9a333944346bbc04cde322a462ed388a739ad93"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bisola Omisore \u003csolaocodes@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1519313 - Do not clear the console input when evaluating and 'devtools.webconsole.input.editor' is true. r=nchevobbe\n\nCreate an `editorMode` prop that is initialized with the preference value, and passed to the JSTerm component.\nThe prop is then used to check if the input should be cleared when an evaluation is done.\nA test is added to ensure this works as expected.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22171", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/components/App.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/components/JSTerm.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/constants.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/reducers/ui.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/store.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/mochitest/browser.ini", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/mochitest/browser_jsterm_editor_execute.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "90de1c90ae69901ff38e5e1c95f9f09ac73313be", "parents": ["b1c9e8f9dab7d6e12b4867f7f7245b5e52b33abf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gurzau Raul \u003crgurzau@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to autoland. a=merge CLOSED TREE", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "6e04cf2319d2c6513fc0d4e5df6cfd42e087d1fe", "parents": ["90de1c90ae69901ff38e5e1c95f9f09ac73313be", "cdb2110b85f32263e6213ee39e6cc9dc37945a03"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Petru Lingurar \u003cpetru.lingurar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1534074 - Use in place api check to prevent Lint ApiDetector errors; r=AndreiLazar\n\nPrevious code was using our own sugary feature26Plus check which Lint doesn't\nproperly follow.\nAs such even if the code was properly guarded and behaved correctly Lint would\nshow errors about improper usage of methods which require higher api levels.\nDoing the api check in place ensures it will get picked up by Lint's\nApiDetector and so it will not report about such errors here.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22889", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/LauncherActivity.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cde32a9377303e91de8854649b704ae082c4cd5f", "parents": ["6e04cf2319d2c6513fc0d4e5df6cfd42e087d1fe"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1466208 - part 42: Clean up PresShell::EventHandler::DispatchEvent() with using early-return style r=smaug\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22460", "files": ["layout/base/PresShell.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3a421f33761b6b852b6b18ee61fb8dc33f8e0d7f", "parents": ["cde32a9377303e91de8854649b704ae082c4cd5f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "jawad \u003cijawadak@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533691 - Uncommented the code and removed TODO comment. r=mak\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22871", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "57f4edb121f34398501c059a98d499ed1c4f5817", "parents": ["3a421f33761b6b852b6b18ee61fb8dc33f8e0d7f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Simon Fraser \u003csfraser@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532236 Reinsert awscli, required for partials caching r=mtabara\n\nReinsert awscli for partials, which is needed for caching. Also update packages and fix the metrics recording\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22942", "files": ["taskcluster/docker/funsize-update-generator/Pipfile", "taskcluster/docker/funsize-update-generator/Pipfile.lock", "taskcluster/docker/funsize-update-generator/scripts/mbsdiff_hook.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7b2ae2ea04957e8f18250ffc62563f301e5335f8", "parents": ["57f4edb121f34398501c059a98d499ed1c4f5817"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mathieu Leplatre \u003cmathieu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533668 - Distinguish manual sync from sync via .get() in uptake Telemetry r=glasserc\n\nDistinguish manual sync from sync via .get() in uptake Telemetry\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22661", "files": ["services/settings/RemoteSettingsClient.jsm", "services/settings/RemoteSettingsComponents.jsm", "services/settings/remote-settings.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Events.yaml", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/collection/uptake.rst"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b64cd61cd5ad1808e19ce76748e9cd44f13cfd95", "parents": ["7b2ae2ea04957e8f18250ffc62563f301e5335f8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreea Pavel \u003capavel@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 7b2ae2ea0495 (bug 1532236) for lint failure", "files": ["taskcluster/docker/funsize-update-generator/Pipfile", "taskcluster/docker/funsize-update-generator/Pipfile.lock", "taskcluster/docker/funsize-update-generator/scripts/mbsdiff_hook.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8076b05b8631a55cc9a9922821e975c4ea4434af", "parents": ["b64cd61cd5ad1808e19ce76748e9cd44f13cfd95"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jason Orendorff \u003cjorendorff@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533413 - Add Symbol.matchAll to list of expected RegExp methods. r=peterv\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22583", "files": ["js/xpconnect/tests/chrome/test_xrayToJS.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "95f9efbbf8051d65db8e0c77aa3eda4893786a12", "parents": ["8076b05b8631a55cc9a9922821e975c4ea4434af"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532946 - Tidy allocation functions by renaming overloads for object and string allocation r=sfink\n\nThis patch attempts to make things clearer by renaming the functions used for allocating objects and strings to AllocateObject and AllocateString, rather than having everything be called Allocate.  Allocate is still used for atoms though which is a little strange but was hard to change.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22275", "files": ["js/src/builtin/TypedObject.cpp", "js/src/gc/Allocator.cpp", "js/src/gc/Allocator.h", "js/src/jit/CodeGenerator.cpp", "js/src/vm/ArrayObject-inl.h", "js/src/vm/Caches-inl.h", "js/src/vm/JSFunction-inl.h", "js/src/vm/N