n be dropped\neven when we are not sweeping.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22715", "files": ["js/src/vm/JSScript.cpp", "js/src/vm/JSScript.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "53c759ed45e4739fafdbb80bbf78376de37d49b0", "parents": ["c1e7e2cb32cdd90af697743ce7dea3303a249977"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533755 - Use RefPtr for SharedScriptData pointers. r=jandem\n\nLeave manual refcounting in the ScriptDataTable for now since it\nrequires a bit of care to make the automatic types do the right thing\nwhen sweeping.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22718", "files": ["js/src/vm/JSScript.cpp", "js/src/vm/JSScript.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "65c88218fbb26505573c73e2ff25fdf1a04d1a7d", "parents": ["53c759ed45e4739fafdbb80bbf78376de37d49b0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533755 - Add SharedScriptData constructor. r=jwalden\n\nThis is based on PrivateScriptData approach. We make sure to call all\ndefault constructors even if the compiler will optimize away.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22717", "files": ["js/src/vm/JSScript.cpp", "js/src/vm/JSScript.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "68d86a52738530fd10d3e0fd9b4dd0b270c89b81", "parents": ["65c88218fbb26505573c73e2ff25fdf1a04d1a7d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "kellykc72 \u003ckellykc72@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530844 - Make push/pop pair for ecx conditional on previous ecx content r=mgaudet\n\nThe ECX register must contain the SHIFT amount. Before this change, ECX will always be push/pop during a SHIFT operation. However, ECX should only be push/pop if it's original contents are going to be overwritten. We now only push/pop ECX if it contains some arbituary value and henc