03e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529883 - Add telemetry instrumentation to count the number of invocations of the element picker. r=gl\n\nAgreed with PM (mbalfanz@mozilla.com) about the intended behavior: number of invocations, not actual picks, is considered sufficient to answer the questions.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22310", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/toolbox.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Scalars.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f115573cf9a82f025084210a0379a0fc84e2436a", "parents": ["eee6b5f77d67da4aeeb6ea34a518e6e1c3de18f0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1524564 - Set aria-activedescendant on the input rather than the view so the input delegates a11y focus. r=Standard8\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23109", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarView.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4619f517e391d5bfa81d27936a2d0c080e8a90bc", "parents": ["f115573cf9a82f025084210a0379a0fc84e2436a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Erica Wright \u003cewright@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533182 - Add Aria attributes to the carat icons in privacy preferences. r=Gijs,flod\n\nAdd tooltiptext to create a name attribute in accessibility tools, add an expanded and collapsed state.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22723", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/privacy.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/privacy.xul", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/preferences/preferences.ftl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f78cbd4bc0307b5fd000195194022613f9d22fc1", "parents": ["4619f517e391d5bfa81d27936a2d0c080e8a90bc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533424 - Don't allow InspectorUtils to mess up with our UA sheets. r=heycam\n\nYou can mess up stuff pretty badly if that happens, and we want to do this\nanyway for the shared UA sheet stuff, so...\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22554", "files": ["dom/tests/mochitest/chrome/test_parsingMode.html", "layout/style/StyleSheet.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5b275de602ae9ecc7fb93dbaf0252747513a0b11", "parents": ["f78cbd4bc0307b5fd000195194022613f9d22fc1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Razvan Caliman \u003crcaliman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1534567 - Ensure inherited CSS variables are case sensitive; r=pbro\n\nBug 1512634 introduced a case-insensitive check for CSS properties. This caused a regression whereby inherited CSS variables with mixed case were incorrectly unmatched when shown in the Rules view.\n\nTo fix this, we do a strict check for CSS variables in CSSProperties front because they are case sensitive (--color and --COLOR are different CSS variables).\nSee: https://www.w3.org/TR/css-variables-1/\n\u003e Unlike other CSS properties, custom property names are case-sensitive.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23113", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/browser.ini", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/browser_rules_variables_03-case-sensitive.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/doc_variables_3.html", "devtools/shared/fronts/css-properties.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5c4d90e31d8c92a7df69e63d7f0624df52fed79f", "parents": ["5b275de602ae9ecc7fb93dbaf0252747513a0b11"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florin Strugariu \u003cfstrugariu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518447 Capture full Mitmproxy logs and have them available as treeherder artifact r=rwood,davehunt,tarek\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21923", "files": ["testing/mozbase/mozproxy/mozproxy/backends/mitm.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "74df776abe146e5f8563e9a040c9c01ee7796e1d", "parents": ["5c4d90e31d8c92a7df69e63d7f0624df52fed79f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530255 - Load keyMap files on demand; r=bgrins.\n\nWe use to include all the keyMap files in the\ncodeMirror bundle, but these files can be\npretty large, and are useless if the user did\nnot select a custom key mapping in the settings\npanel.\nThis patch changes this to only load those files\nwhen they are needed, either when a new editor\nis created, or when the user changes the key mapping\npreference. The files are only loaded once.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22977", "files": ["devtools/client/jar.mn", "devtools/client/shared/sourceeditor/codemirror/codemirror.bundle.js", "devtools/client/shared/sourceeditor/editor.js", "devtools/client/shared/sourceeditor/test/browser_editor_prefs.js", "devtools/client/shared/sourceeditor/test/codemirror/codemirror.html", "devtools/client/shared/sourceeditor/test/codemirror/vimemacs.html", "devtools/client/shared/sourceeditor/webpack.config.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2f7c1341cc1e39358cf79de3dc476c0104ae8279", "parents": ["74df776abe146e5f8563e9a040c9c01ee7796e1d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Stephen Donner \u003cstephen.donner@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Fix bug 1532772.  klling typo in console-log message r=rwood,Bebe\n\nFix \"klling\" typo in Talos console-log message\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23066", "files": ["testing/talos/talos/mitmproxy/mitmproxy.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "016a77373b3ac9702baf2f75043c646e2925fc28", "parents": ["2f7c1341cc1e39358cf79de3dc476c0104ae8279"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1493948 - Package binary of geckodriver into its own artifact. r=jlorenzo\n\nThis task extracts the binary of geckodriver from the\ncommon test package and stores it into its own artifact.\nFor now this task is only run after Nightly build tasks\non supported platforms..\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23094", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/config.yml", "taskcluster/ci/geckodriver-repack/kind.yml", "taskcluster/docs/kinds.rst"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "eba70db52fa545d7e16047948e06506ab9ade728", "parents": ["016a77373b3ac9702baf2f75043c646e2925fc28"], "tags": []}, {"author": "yulia \u003cystartsev@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529247 - remove unused releaseMany method from thread client and actor; r=ochameau\n\nThere is one spot I am unsure about, and that is the test:\ndevtools/server/tests/unit/test_threadlifetime-06.js -- should this be kept or do we want to remove\nit as well?\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21674", "files": ["devtools/docs/backend/protocol.md", "devtools/server/actors/thread.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_threadlifetime-03.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_threadlifetime-05.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_threadlifetime-06.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/xpcshell.ini", "devtools/shared/client/thread-client.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aa554fe5d8fe9c2392b1d3daaa2757d2763636d1", "parents": ["eba70db52fa545d7e16047948e06506ab9ade728"], "tags": []}, {"author": "yulia \u003cystartsev@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529247 - remove unused cachedScript property; r=ochameau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21672", "files": ["devtools/shared/client/thread-client.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4cb9ab350bcb8afdee1b27aa970e75a8577d7bd9", "parents": ["aa554fe5d8fe9c2392b1d3daaa2757d2763636d1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mathieu Leplatre \u003cmathieu@mozilla.com\u003e", "