node": "aff09871d5b9708857345e9a8922cd25926a0323", "parents": ["b10035bbdc3a54b7fcc0d0f5dfb44e4f090a5651"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Varga \u003cjan.varga@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1535995 - Check that group information is up to date; r=asuth a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23822", "files": ["dom/localstorage/test/unit/groupMismatch_profile.zip", "dom/localstorage/test/unit/test_groupMismatch.js", "dom/localstorage/test/unit/xpcshell.ini", "dom/quota/ActorsParent.cpp", "dom/quota/test/unit/groupMismatch_profile.zip", "dom/quota/test/unit/test_groupMismatch.js", "dom/quota/test/unit/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3cbb28dba0fae5d589a2cd1584dbbcaa0255b2c7", "parents": ["aff09871d5b9708857345e9a8922cd25926a0323"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Varga \u003cjan.varga@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1535995 - Quick followup patch to fix an ESlint failure; r=asuth a=pascalc", "files": ["dom/localstorage/test/unit/test_groupMismatch.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1962a2d9ec9af138c578c331c9082b5e2af6cd36", "parents": ["3cbb28dba0fae5d589a2cd1584dbbcaa0255b2c7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Woodrow \u003cmwoodrow@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1525372 - Add background-clip:text rendering observer so that we get notified of changes to the clipped contents. r=jwatt a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20110", "files": ["layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp", "layout/svg/SVGObserverUtils.cpp", "layout/svg/SVGObserverUtils.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e4ee5e511a6fe4534b6caa153e219317c7c23e27", "parents": ["1962a2d9ec9af138c578c331c9082b5e2af6cd36"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Woodrow \u003cmwoodrow@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1525372 - Add WPT reftest for moving background-clip:text text contents without invalidating the text frame. r=emilio a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20111", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-backgrounds/background-clip/clip-text-dynamic-2-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-backgrounds/background-clip/clip-text-dynamic-2.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "77a1f36d6cad9ce36bff4c187c0ca4111d7efc78", "parents": ["e4ee5e511a6fe4534b6caa153e219317c7c23e27"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Froman \u003cmfroman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530305 - handle failure to alloc Shmem in RemoteVideoDecoderParent. r=jya a=pascalc\n\n- Modify ProcessDecodedData to return a MediaResult.\n- RemoteDecoderParent::RecvInput and RemoteDecoderParent::RecvDrain\n  both use error returned from ProcessDecodedData to call SendError.\n- RemoteVideoDecoderParent and RemoteAudioDecoderParent both return\n  MediaResult with NS_ERROR_OUT_OF_MEMORY if AllocShmem fails in\n  ProcessDecodedData (or if the returned buffer size is less than\n  the requested size).\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23988", "files": ["dom/media/ipc/RemoteAudioDecoder.cpp", "dom/media/ipc/RemoteAudioDecoder.h", "dom/media/ipc/RemoteDecoderParent.cpp", "dom/media/ipc/RemoteDecoderParent.h", "dom/media/ipc/RemoteVideoDecoder.cpp", "dom/media/ipc/RemoteVideoDecoder.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "17ada400a1db301d6717440a56364f0b4dddc984", "parents": ["77a1f36d6cad9ce36bff4c187c0ca4111d7efc78"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1531333 - Fix \u003csvg:use\u003e cycle detection. r=longsonr a=pascalc\n\nWith the current code we'll eventually detect the cycle, but will take much\nmore, creating many shadow trees unnecessarily. Take for example the following:\n\n\u003csvg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" width=\"133\" height=\"232774\"\u003e\n    \u003cstyle\u003e\n      symbol { display: block }\n    \u003c/style\u003e\n    \u003csymbol id=\"svg-sprite\" viewBox=\"0 0 133 230866\"\u003e\n        \u003ctitle\u003esvg-sprite\u003c/title\u003e\n        \u003csymbol id=\"svg-sprite\" viewBox=\"0 0 133 230866\"\u003e\n            \u003ctitle\u003esvg-sprite\u003c/title\u003e\n            \u003cuse xlink:href=\"#svg-sprite\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" /\u003e\n        \u003c/symbol\u003e\n        \u003cuse xlink:href=\"#svg-sprite\" y=\"1601\" width=\"133\" height=\"228958\" /\u003e\n    \u003c/symbol\u003e\n    \u003cuse xlink:href=\"#svg-sprite\" y=\"1601\" width=\"133\" height=\"230866\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\nBefore this patch, we'd create an svg use element subtree for #svg-sprite. That\nsubtree will contain two other \u003cuse\u003e elements, one under the \u003csymbol\u003e, one not\nunder it.\n\nBoth point to #svg-sprite, but we fail to detect we're an ancestor since the\nelement #svg-sprite we're looking at is the clone of the #svg-sprite element.\n\nThus we need to take a look at mOriginal instead (which is the \u003cuse\u003e element\nunder #svg-sprite) rather than at the clone.\n\nYeah, I had to draw the trees, it's messy :)\n\nBlink and WebKit do something slightly different (they check the element id\ndirectly[1]). That's not 100% correct, since you can have multiple elements with\nthe same ID.\n\n[1]: https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/blink/renderer/core/svg/svg_use_element.cc?l=560&rcl=861855dcb8c39ba8d42497247d433277858df79b\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24565", "files": ["dom/svg/SVGUseElement.cpp", "dom/svg/SVGUseElement.h", "layout/svg/tests/mochitest.ini", "layout/svg/tests/test_use_tree_cycle.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ae13953b50050a116254bd80244b479907046f27", "parents": ["17ada400a1db301d6717440a56364f0b4dddc984"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Petru Lingurar \u003cpetru.lingurar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1534213 - Reduce the number of WebpageItemRow layout refreshes; r=JanH a=pascalc\n\nPreviously, WebpageItemRow's layout would be updated everytime a new Tab for\nit's url would be ADDED/CLOSED/LOCATION_CHANGED to force a recheck of the need\nto show the \"Switch to tab hint\".\nTo prevent multiple layout refreshes for every such event we will check the\ncurrent display status of the \"Switch to tab hint\" against the newly computed\nvalue after an ADDED/CLOSED/LOCATION_CHANGED event was received.\nEagerly changing the value for 'switchToTabHintShown' along with informing\nabout the need for layout refresh to prevent any race conditions between\nreceiving more events and actualy refreshing the layout.\n(In my tests I saw ADDED/LOCATION_CHANGE refreshing the same layout needlessly)\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24013", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/activitystream/homepanel/stream/WebpageItemRow.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8c19d4132c70122a35d3115c0af65e3bf14cee1d", "parents": ["ae13953b50050a116254bd80244b479907046f27"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1535584 - Restore UpdateCodecFrameSize to vp9_impl.cc; r=bwc a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23713", "files": ["media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_coding/codecs/vp9/vp9_impl.cc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "851a8b3844769ddc6d484be1eb8d40ab69f1ae8c", "parents": ["8c19d4132c70122a35d3115c0af65e3bf14cee1d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1553515036, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "10908": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=re