nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nda -\u003e 737ad76752a9\nit -\u003e bf15bb3b1ea3\nka -\u003e ca5609068e0e\nnl -\u003e f81f01c0cacf", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a9640f9abe520b20a48d34254688582fc1345f24", "parents": ["76b560fe9809e9d4c74a7a3927e917ededce2239"], "tags": []}], "date": 1553936426, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10954": {"changesets": [{"author": "Dennis Schubert \u003cdschubert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539618 - Remove superfluous dot from use_legacy_keycode_and_charcode pref. r=miketaylr a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25125", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d8560229d39e4c25dc5f34e7852ef8bcb91a7f96", "parents": ["a9640f9abe520b20a48d34254688582fc1345f24"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Randall Barker \u003crbarker@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500719 - Ensure toolbar is hidden when going fullscreen r=botond a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24348", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/AndroidDynamicToolbarAnimator.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b98051a74254284a3479e0ae2136368ea3ac596c", "parents": ["d8560229d39e4c25dc5f34e7852ef8bcb91a7f96"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1534749 - Handle shutdown races between the compositor thread and IPDL object setup. r=rhunt a=pascalc\n\nWhen the compositor thread has begun shutdown, it will spin the event\nloop for the main thread until the last CompositorThreadHolder reference\nhas been released. While spinning, new IPDL objects may be attempted to\nbe created which depend on the compositor thread; we should check to\nensure the compositor thread is still around before proceeding with\ncreation. These objects include CompositorManagerParent,\nImageBridgeParent, and VRManagerParent. Additionally there is a very\nsimilar bug between the vsync thread and VsyncBridgeChild.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23308", "files": ["gfx/ipc/GPUProcessManager.cpp", "gfx/ipc/VsyncBridgeChild.cpp", "gfx/ipc/VsyncBridgeChild.h", "gfx/ipc/VsyncIOThreadHolder.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorManagerParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorManagerParent.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/ImageBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/vr/ipc/VRManagerParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "169d315489fe1d36d19587c7a07b47f9ce8eebb0", "parents": ["b98051a74254284a3479e0ae2136368ea3ac596c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "dlee \u003cdlee@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1535307 - Remove an extra bracket when set update status in aboutUrlClassifier. r=Gijs a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24172", "files": ["toolkit/content/aboutUrlClassifier.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b4d3f8ae02748dd0cf3d5aa3e496d38d0ac65b88", "parents": ["169d315489fe1d36d19587c7a07b47f9ce8eebb0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Justin Wood \u003cCallek@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1535393 - Fill in the correct MSI version number for release and ESR. r=mhowell,nalexander a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24994", "files": ["browser/installer/windows/msi/installer.wxs", "python/mozbuild/mozbuild/repackaging/msi.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1b9b7c6da0c3454d1434d67a2d143ef56b44d8d8", "parents": ["b4d3f8ae02748dd0cf3d5aa3e496d38d0ac65b88"], "tags": []}, {"author": "vladikoff \u003cvlad.filippov@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539211 - Enable the Firefox Accounts pairing preference. r=eoger a=pascalc\n\nEnables the FxA pairing preference after rounds of QA.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24932", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "afe17b3276dad6530086634cf49f09917d8aee44", "parents": ["1b9b7c6da0c3454d1434d67a2d143ef56b44d8d8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eitan Isaacson \u003ceitan@monotonous.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1538021 - Use owner of WindowEventDispatcher as window for messaging. r=yzen a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24442", "files": ["accessible/jsat/AccessFu.jsm", "accessible/jsat/ContentControl.jsm", "accessible/jsat/Traversal.jsm", "accessible/jsat/Utils.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4ebcdc4fd000d0fe0c4f9efd5b629c0bc4167b4e", "parents": ["afe17b3276dad6530086634cf49f09917d8aee44"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Erica Wright \u003cewright@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518807 - Icons and images are visible on high contrast mode. r=jaws a=pascalc\n\nHigh contrast mode does not render background images, set as list-style image instead. Fix fill colors for other icons.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23943", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/incontentprefs/privacy.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f97ab548d6f1f30cca81c743364ba560d50b8222", "parents": ["4ebcdc4fd000d0fe0c4f9efd5b629c0bc4167b4e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1553957834, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "nerli@mozilla.com"}, "10955": {"changesets": [{"author": "Bryce Van Dyk \u003cbvandyk@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1537675 - Ensure reads in VPXDecoder.cpp happen in correct order. r=jya a=pascalc\n\nFunction arguments may not evaluate in order, as such, this ensures width is read\nbefore height from VP9 streams.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24372", "files": ["dom/media/platforms/agnostic/VPXDecoder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "111a68271a2dfc91a27d30a1496024728ebaa5ce", "parents": ["f97ab548d6f1f30cca81c743364ba560d50b8222"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1512472 - Hold nsHttpConnectionInfo in a RefPtr to avoid leak when returning early r=dragana a=pascalc\n\nnsHttpConnectionMgr::SpeculativeConnect may return early, without assigning ci to a RefPtr. In that case, we'd leak the nsHttpConnectionInfo. We need to have it in a RefPtr from the start to make sure we can't leak it.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23497", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b2fad2fe236ef5607b2dba3cb5fb360b1197af1", "parents": ["111a68271a2dfc91a27d30a1496024728ebaa5ce"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Felipe Gomes \u003cfelipc@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539311 - Fix incorrect parameter in the Windows Taskbar Previews code. r=Standard8 a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25013", "files": ["browser/modules/WindowsPreviewPerTab.jsm", "toolkit/components/thumbnails/PageThumbs.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "98acf3216e5a3445f7da68960fa51a1f53e65163", "parents": ["3b2fad2fe236ef5607b2dba3cb5fb360b1197af1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Noorenberghe \u003cmozilla@noorenberghe.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533925 - Allow about: pages to be forced into the extension process. r=kmag a=pascalc\n\nSome extensions want to implement about: pages and we want those pages to be loaded in the extension process, not in the web content process, so that:\n1) a compromised web process won't get access to the about: page content\n2) the extension page can use all the APIs that extension pages normally get, instead of only content script APIs.\n\nPost-Fission we will need to know which extension process to choose.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24989", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/general/browser_e10s_about_process.js", "netwerk/protocol/about/nsIAboutModule.idl", "toolkit/modules/E10SUtils.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d7c011c3dd7f589362c64829a28f7f42991937c5", "parents": ["98acf3216e5a3445f7da68960fa51a1f53e65163"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Felipe Gomes \u003cfelipc@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539255 - Back out new tab animations. r=dao a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24964", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/base/content/browser.css", "browser/base/content/tabbrowser.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d511bf7fa222cfac860067f72bb11c6691b50a20", "parents": ["d7c011c3dd7f589362c64829a28f7f42991937c5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Beich \u003cjbeich@FreeBSD.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530659 - Always pass -Isilk/fixed to unbreak on aarch64 after bug 1522016. r=glandium a=pascalc", "files": ["media/libopus/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dba7de840829244c8978c16dfc4a7123aaa19610", "parents": ["d511bf7fa222cfac860067f72bb11c6691b50a20"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mathieu Leplatre \u003cmathieu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539101 - Force extra values to be strings in Uptake Telemetry r=glasserc a=pascalc\n\nForce extra values to be strings in Uptake Telemetry\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25040", "files": ["services/common/tests/unit/test_uptake_telemetry.js", "services/common/uptake-telemetry.js", "services/settings/RemoteSettingsClient.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f9c39d67b0d6c8b192af593ed98e8ae71f567734", "parents": ["dba7de840829244c8978c16dfc4a7123aaa19610"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532850 - Check the return value of LookAndFeel::GetInt() in case of the function failure. r=emilio a=pascalc\n\nActually the function will fail on Android since on xpcshell tests we don't\ninitialize AndroidBridge so that we can't query the corresponding system\nsettings.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22270", "files": ["layout/style/nsMediaFeatures.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "33a8d0d55cf4b7d419a8c5803a9ac234d3d330fb", "parents": ["f9c39d67b0d6c8b192af593ed98e8ae71f567734"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532850 - Implement the backend for prefers-color-scheme on Android. r=geckoview-reviewers,snorp a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22272", "files": ["mobile/android/base/AndroidManifest.xml.in", "mobile/android/geckoview/api.txt", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoSystemStateListener.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoRuntime.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoView.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/doc-files/CHANGELOG.md", "widget/android/nsLookAndFeel.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c744534702892c60350398ce2d3bd41ebdd3f43b", "parents": ["33a8d0d55cf4b7d419a8c5803a9ac234d3d330fb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528319 - Don't create a Promise when shutting down an AudioContext. r=karlt a=pascalc\n\nThis is done in the same style as `::Suspend` and `::Resume`.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24515", "files": ["dom/media/webaudio/AudioContext.cpp", "dom/media/webaudio/AudioContext.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "44b4f787bfeb2e6888e58488dfec84acafc15941", "parents": ["c744534702892c60350398ce2d3bd41ebdd3f43b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1538546 - Hide incognito checkbox in addon-installed notification for not_allowed extensions. r=mixedpuppy,kmag a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24719", "files": ["browser/modules/ExtensionsUI.jsm", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/internal/XPIDatabase.jsm", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_extension_sideloading_permission.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_webapi_install.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_webapi_theme.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_webext_incognito.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8935c8db2301fb744209e76212a4222bd0d4ede7", "parents": ["44b4f787bfeb2e6888e58488dfec84acafc15941"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1538546 - Check AddonManager PERM_CAN_CHANGE_PRIVATEBROWSING_ACCESS permission instead of the incognito manifest property. r=kmag,mixedpuppy a=pascalc\n\nDepends on D24719\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24720", "files": ["browser/modules/ExtensionsUI.jsm", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "381133904780a376d4991883a605457b2faecc86", "parents": ["8935c8db2301fb744209e76212a4222bd0d4ede7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1553962200, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "nerli@mozilla.com"}, "10956": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1462911 - allow for new overflown items to be the first item in the overflow list, r=jaws a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24944", "files": ["browser/components/customizableui/CustomizableUI.jsm", "browser/components/customizableui/test/browser_914138_widget_API_overflowable_toolbar.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cb8b50a3dc6addd0e25b0de62802bbbcbaa8bd8a", "parents": ["381133904780a376d4991883a605457b2faecc86"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1536157 - Schedule a paint when setting a pending visual scroll update. r=kats a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23901", "files": ["layout/base/PresShell.cpp", "layout/base/nsIPresShell.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e0b94caff888c14d80461bfa414a90ac11515184", "parents": ["cb8b50a3dc6addd0e25b0de62802bbbcbaa8bd8a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1536157 - Make sure we repaint after accepting a visual scroll update. r=kats a=pascalc\n\nA possible alternative would be to have the main thread already paint a\ndisplayport at the target position of a requested visual update as part of\nthe same transaction that requests the update.\n\nThere are a couple of reasons we may not want to do that:\n\n 1) APZ could reject the requested visual update under certain conditions,\n    e.g. if there is a higher-priority layout update.\n\n 2) It would break the property that the displayport in the main thread's\n    scroll metadata is relative to the scroll offset in said metadata.\n    Various places assume this and untangling that seems tricky.\n\nThis does mean that if the main thread requests a visual update to \"far away\"\n(outside the existing displayport), we can get temporary checkerboarding\nbefore the content at the target position is painted. However, it's\nstraightforward for callers to work around that, by changing the layout scroll\noffset _and_ scheduling a visual update if they wish to visual-scroll far\naway.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23902", "files": ["gfx/layers/RepaintRequest.h", "gfx/layers/apz/src/AsyncPanZoomController.cpp", "layout/base/nsIPresShell.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f36792ee434476ad27f215563b2fda30f6b7298b", "parents": ["e0b94caff888c14d80461bfa414a90ac11515184"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1536459 add messages for different private permission conditions r=flod,aswan a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24990", "files": ["toolkit/locales/en-US/toolkit/about/aboutAddons.ftl", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.xul", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_webext_incognito.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2a43c0f29c287054b941988970db92a64e5519be", "parents": ["f36792ee434476ad27f215563b2fda30f6b7298b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Swan \u003caswan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1537723 Enable LWT updates on Android r=mixedpuppy a=pascalc\n\nAlso ensure that LightweightThemeManager.updateOneTheme() returns\neven if the update request fails.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24981", "files": ["mobile/android/app/mobile.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/LightweightThemeManager.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0f768a9686b19f26c36483fe67fbe6fb913c8499", "parents": ["2a43c0f29c287054b941988970db92a64e5519be"], "tags": []}], "date": 1553972126, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "cbrindusan@mozilla.com"}, "10957": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncs -\u003e 3380c3c42f0b\ncy -\u003e 163f6592779d\