a -\u003e ca801d7d469f\ncak -\u003e 608e2e1ac922\ncs -\u003e d4742f10cf9e", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "26d09facf5d13a086db8a58335e0293d865ca873", "parents": ["f388d98e8d63b30b2f43e199c57249c0d75fa072"], "tags": []}], "date": 1554717626, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11030": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1536447 - Use HeapPtr rather than Heap pointer wrappers in ctypes r=sfink a=pascalc", "files": ["js/src/ctypes/CTypes.cpp", "js/src/ctypes/CTypes.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "340c569378b94bba026080ad8f42e494637fb3f3", "parents": ["26d09facf5d13a086db8a58335e0293d865ca873"], "tags": []}], "date": 1554718317, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "jcoppeard@mozilla.com"}, "11031": {"changesets": [{"author": "Dave Townsend \u003cdtownsend@oxymoronical.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539820: Fix test_claim_locked.js to work with dev-edition. r=Gijs a=test-only\n\nThe original name of the profile is irrelevant here since we aren't testing\na migration to profiles-per-install. On dev-edition DEDICATED_NAME is the same\nas PROFILE_DEFAULT so we correctly make a new profile with a unique name.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26230", "files": ["toolkit/profile/xpcshell/test_claim_locked.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cc0d59ec03cfabb3b2c3e0aa8f92c9628bfb99bc", "parents": ["340c569378b94bba026080ad8f42e494637fb3f3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lars T Hansen \u003clhansen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1535194 - Always check error return from BufferOffset::diffB.  r=luke a=pascalc\n\nWe were missing error checks at two points.  In one case an error\nreturn is meaningful; in another case it is not, as the problem should\nhave been guarded against at a higher level by emitting far jump\nislands soon enough during pasteup of compiled code.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23506", "files": ["js/src/jit/arm/Assembler-arm.cpp", "js/src/jit/arm/MacroAssembler-arm.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e964138e796b526597daac4125a79dca43233c6e", "parents": ["cc0d59ec03cfabb3b2c3e0aa8f92c9628bfb99bc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532465 - Ensure we AddRef prior to early return in MediaType::Assign; r=pehrsons a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D23143", "files": ["media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/windows/MediaType.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "97b3d94e492d245ce71546550af6a6b6e54917b2", "parents": ["e964138e796b526597daac4125a79dca43233c6e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nika Layzell \u003cnika@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1536405 - Cycle-collect through ChromeEventHandler. r=bz a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com//D24982", "files": ["docshell/base/nsDocShell.cpp", "docshell/base/nsDocShell.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "def85b90d5e4d7fd846cbba7c96ee02989abad9d", "parents": ["97b3d94e492d245ce71546550af6a6b6e54917b2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Olli Pettay \u003cOlli.Pettay@helsinki.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1540166, avoid some useless ForgetSkippable handling while we're already dealing with snow-white objects, r=mccr8 a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25414", "files": ["xpcom/base/nsCycleCollector.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1cdd67f491bf9e8de3a8bfa052c72ed6f0e9654f", "parents": ["def85b90d5e4d7fd846cbba7c96ee02989abad9d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jed Davis \u003cjld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1516325. r=glandium a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22638", "files": ["config/external/nspr/pr/moz.build", "toolkit/xre/nsAppRunner.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d8cb02604219e560b7d15f73667e3f0015ae02ea", "parents": ["1cdd67f491bf9e8de3a8bfa052c72ed6f0e9654f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan Hunt \u003crhunt@eqrion.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1516425 - Hold a strong reference to TabParent from nsFrameLoader and make TabParent cycle collected. r=smaug a=pascalc\n\nCurrently TabParent is refcounted, but nsFrameLoader hold a weak pointer. The pointer\nshould be cleared out when the TabParent is destroyed, but that's a bit of a footgun\nand it's not obvious that we always do this correctly.\n\nBecause TabParent holds a reference to a nsFrameLoader and the frame element (which\ncontains a nsFrameLoader), I think this means we need to cycle collect TabParent.", "files": ["dom/base/nsFrameLoader.cpp", "dom/base/nsFrameLoader.h", "dom/ipc/TabParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/TabParent.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fceed60b10ce9ca9b022b73d769f6a070c859339", "parents": ["d8cb02604219e560b7d15f73667e3f0015ae02ea"], "tags": []}], "date": 1554719836, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "11032": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncy -\u003e 06d7fcaa67c5\nde -\u003e ff661197f585", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "650cabd8d8a060bf3bf37daadbdccd4dea585755", "parents": ["fceed60b10ce9ca9b022b73d769f6a070c859339"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncy -\u003e 06d7fcaa67c5\nda -\u003e 7334df5377