site data settings UI to use cropping. r=jaws,flod a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25692", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/siteData/browser_siteData3.js", "browser/components/preferences/siteDataSettings.js", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/preferences/siteDataSettings.ftl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7b5b8c302a1ab509c7e995254f0e7a809db07327", "parents": ["bfdb7d766a6d6a817db48093f78b1391d50e53e9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bas Schouten \u003cbschouten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1538666: Fix typo in PathCapture::TransformedCopyToBuilder. r=rhunt a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26335", "files": ["gfx/2d/PathCapture.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a692fdeb597b58fc21c0237aee9adf7540c72695", "parents": ["7b5b8c302a1ab509c7e995254f0e7a809db07327"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nathan Froyd \u003cfroydnj@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1520929 - part 1 - add an isWowARM64 property to nsSystemInfo; r=aklotz a=pascalc\n\nIn addition to knowing whether we're running x86-on-x86-64, we'd also\nlike to know about the x86-on-arm64 case.  The current code doesn't\nprovide enough information to determine that, so we need to query a\nlittle bit harder.", "files": ["xpcom/base/nsSystemInfo.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "063a0c6b1078ab9bab8e66c35ac41809d173da7f", "parents": ["a692fdeb597b58fc21c0237aee9adf7540c72695"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nathan Froyd \u003cfroydnj@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1520929 - part 2 - send isWowARM64 through telemetry; r=chutten,data-review=chutten a=pascalc", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/app/TelemetryEnvironment.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/data/environment.rst", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_TelemetryEnvironment.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4a094d23761cc23c04460fb6373beee85542c069", "parents": ["063a0c6b1078ab9bab8e66c35ac41809d173da7f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1554906463, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ncsoregi@mozilla.com"}, "11057": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nathan Froyd \u003cfroydnj@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1535301 - turn off ICF for Windows builds; r=chmanchester a=pascalc\n\nWe're doing this to try and gather some information on crashes that have\nstacks affected by ICF, particularly on beta.  We plan to revert this\npatch after we've gathered crashes for a day or two.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com//D26765", "files": ["python/mozbuild/mozbuild/frontend/context.py", "python/mozbuild/mozbuild/test/frontend/test_emitter.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1ec10dce28e2587acb3329f89b600555ce54e315", "parents": ["4a094d23761cc23c04460fb6373beee85542c069"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1538042 Part 1: Change nsIFind::Find to have access to text length. r=mccr8 a=abillings\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25005", "files": ["toolkit/components/find/nsFind.cpp", "toolkit/components/find/nsIFind.idl", "toolkit/components/find/nsWebBrowserFind.cpp", "toolkit/components/typeaheadfind/nsTypeAheadFind.cpp", "toolkit/components/windowcreator/test/test_nsFind.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "828f8931afe0bc0f686c5a9143ce953c1f086587", "parents": ["1ec10dce28e2587acb3329f89b600555ce54e315"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dave Townsend \u003cdtownsend@oxymoronical.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1542221: Correctly save the state of nsIToolkitProfileService.startWithLastProfile. r=Gijs a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26576", "files": ["toolkit/profile/nsToolkitProfileService.cpp", "toolkit/profile/xpcshell/head.js", "toolkit/profile/xpcshell/test_clean.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8842c0d0cef24b7eff3550daed701ae33cb6ec7d", "parents": ["828f8931afe0bc0f686c5a9143ce953c1f086587"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1542829 - Backport an upstream libpng patch. r=aosmond a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26575", "files": ["media/libpng/png.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e52e74683afcfd9434253927cc54c9081b28a187", "parents": ["8842c0d0cef24b7eff3550daed701ae33cb6ec7d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1541580 - Cleanup ProxyObject creation r=jandem a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26157", "files": ["js/src/vm/ProxyObject.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "590d0706d113fca9c085f866f3c7ea29955cc8e2", "parents": ["e52e74683afcfd9434253927cc54c9081b28a187"], "tags": []}], "date": 1554908176, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "11058": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henri Sivonen \u003chsivonen@hsivonen.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1541088 - Revert focus-related Fission event delivery changes on beta. r=nika a=pascalc\n\nThis changeset reverts:\n\n* Bug 1524231 - Find TabParent to dispatch to by LayersId attached to the event.\n* Bug 1532334 - Make nsContentUtils::IsSubDocumentTabbable() return true for out-of-process iframes.\n* Bug 1524980 - Use RemoteFrameChild if present in nsFocusManager::Focus().\n* Bug 1524977 - Use RemoteFrameChild if present in nsFocusManager::GetNextTabbableContent().\n* Bug 1534258 - Send Deactivate() messages to out-of-process iframes.\n* Bug 1534255 - Enable out-of-process iframes to take APZ focus.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com//D26689", "files": ["dom/base/nsContentUtils.cpp", "dom/base/nsFocusManager.cpp", "dom/base/nsFrameLoader.cpp", "dom/base/nsFrameLoader.h", "dom/events/EventStateManager.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserBridgeChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserBridgeChild.h", "dom/ipc/BrowserBridgeParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserBridgeParent.h", "dom/ipc/PBrowserBridge.ipdl", "dom/ipc/TabParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/FocusTarget.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "661df9ccbd0de5eda56c3cf0a766c2ddcee3abbe", "parents": ["590d0706d113fca9c085f866f3c7ea29955cc8e2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1538708 - Stop storing sockets in adb-client.js;r=ochameau a=pascalc\n\nThe client close() method is not used anywhere. Individual callers should be responsible for closing opened sockets if needed.\nRemoving this method and the _sockets array, we no longer leak strings when calling adb.updateRuntimes()\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25213", "files": ["devtools/shared/adb/adb-client.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1796fcfc0b87f938ad8d1e7a584ca5fbf2c56ffe", "parents": ["661df9ccbd0de5eda56c3cf0a766c2ddcee3abbe"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1541113 - Avoid crashing content process with giant drawtarget. r=mstange a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25931", "files": ["gfx/tests/crashtests/1541113.html", "gfx/tests/crashtests/crashtests.list", "layout/svg/nsFilterInstance.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9b56acdef604faeee96eb7cdb1369d8f2cf97042", "parents": ["1796fcfc0b87f938ad8d1e7a584ca5fbf2c56ffe"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Marco Bonardo \u003cmbonardo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1541399 - Ensure we don't fetch search suggestions for file urls. r=adw a=pascalc\n\nFixes the tokenizer to recognize file:/// urls, plus adds a second layer of\nprotection, so that if URI fixup thinks the typed string may be an url, we don't\nfetch suggestions for it.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26282", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarTokenizer.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/unit/test_tokenizer.js", "toolkit/components/places/UnifiedComplete.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "59dcec156ac92fac1b57e640a2e3222df604aa4e", "parents": ["9b56acdef604faeee96eb7cdb1369d8f2cf97042"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henri Sivonen \u003chsivonen@hsivonen.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1536575 - Stack size on aarch64 Windows should match stack size on x86_64 Windows. r=glandium a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26272", "files": ["config/config.mk", "layout/reftests/bugs/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "611f3e691f0b918b449e7a1717d08d20e7b509f9", "parents": ["59dcec156ac92fac1b57e640a2e3222df604aa4e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Shal \u003cmshal@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1536194 - Fix uses of MOZ_LTO in a few mozconfigs; r=firefox-build-system-reviewers,glandium a=npotb\n\nAfter bug 1530908 changed LTO to be environment driven, the macosx64\nnightly mozconfig enables LTO by setting MOZ_LTO=1. The add-on-devel\nmozconfig tried to disable LTO by using --disable-lto, but the\nenvironment variable takes precedence, leaving LTO enabled for these\nbuilds. This pushed the build time up to be close to the max runtime for\nthe task, causing frequent intermittent failures.\n\nWe should 'unset MOZ_LTO' everywhere that --disable-lto was used, and\n'export MOZ_LTO=1' everywhere --enable-lto was used.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26608", "files": ["browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/profile-use", "browser/config/mozconfigs/macosx64/add-on-devel", "browser/config/mozconfigs/macosx64/code-coverage", "browser/config/mozconfigs/macosx64/nightly-fuzzing-asan"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "480b514d559f1036f6f51b7bca8c0652706df31b", "parents": ["611f3e691f0b918b449e7a1717d08d20e7b509f9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1554921220, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "11059": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gabriele Svelto \u003cgsvelto@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1536850 - Properly detect when the browser is shutting down to avoid taking content process minidumps too late r=Ehsan a=pascalc\n\nThis code was already present but it had two flaws: the first one was that the\nvariable used to prevent minidumps from being taken when shutting down was not\nbeing initialized which caused it to be true most of the time and thus\nprevented captures even in valid scenarios. The second was that we relied on\nthe \"profile-before-change\" change event to detect shutdown but this often\nhappens after we've already started closing tabs and shutting down processes\nthus the minidump generation would often race against it.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24691", "files": ["dom/ipc/ContentParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/ContentParent.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6a427ed74d6533bde36358c434af42d5da67b891", "parents": ["480b514d559f1036f6f51b7bca8c0652706df31b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1536159 - Crash diagnositic for js::TypeZone::addPendingRecompile. r=jwalden a=pascalc\n\nRecord the size of allocation in crashreporter to determine if these are\ngenuine small OOM or if something problematic has happened.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25152", "files": ["js/src/vm/TypeInference.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1452b03b01d45740bd3f54a15f95360fcc0597a5", "parents": ["6a427ed74d6533bde36358c434af42d5da67b891"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1543166 - Add missing null check in IonBuilder::computeHeapType. r=tcampbell a=pascalc\n\nSummary: getObject can return nullptr when the TypeSet uses a TypeHashSet for the objects.\n\nReviewers: tcampbell\n\nReviewed By: tcampbell\n\nBug #: 1543166\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26874", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/ion/bug1543166.js", "js/src/jit/IonBuilder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "11ddfc9bd642f08e487fb76d23b7626f0b179e58", "parents": ["1452b03b01d45740bd3f54a15f95360fcc0597a5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1554950211, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "dvarga@mozilla.com"}, "11060": {"changesets": [{"author": "Daniel Varga \u003cdvarga@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 3 changesets (bug 1543166, bug 1536159, bug 1536850) for build bustage at builds/worker/workspace/build/src/dom/ipc/ContentParent.cpp a=backout\n\nBacked out changeset 11ddfc9bd642 (bug 1543166)\nBacked out changeset 1452b03b01d4 (bug 1536159)\nBacked out changeset 6a427ed74d65 (bug 1536850)", "files": ["dom/ipc/ContentParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/ContentParent.h", "js/src/jit-test/tests/ion/bug1543166.js", "js/src/jit/IonBuilder.cpp", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "92601d63125e1c4f043a665476ab8cea39c9e592", "parents": ["11ddfc9bd642f08e487fb76d23b7626f0b179e58"], "tags": []}], "date": 1554952987, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "dvarga@mozilla.com"}, "11061": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbr -\u003e 85b9ed36cf6d\ncy -\u003e bbcfba346b0a\nda -\u003e fe002aea8751\ndsb -\u003e 11d1f57cc72d\nes-AR -\u003e 48bbe0f29b39\nes-MX -\u003e be605c0b5201\nfr -\u