nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25538", "files": ["browser/themes/linux/browser.css", "browser/themes/osx/browser.css", "browser/themes/windows/browser.css", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_themes_findbar.js", "toolkit/themes/shared/findBar.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "626e61fede41425cdde82038435fb53d97786032", "parents": ["34cfebee50385ae0fedd76ee32772cb93082022d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alexis Beingessner \u003ca.beingessner@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1525642 - ensure that w~=1 when assuming a transform is just a translation. r=gw a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D27163", "files": ["gfx/wr/webrender/src/util.rs", "gfx/wr/wrench/reftests/transforms/reftest.list", "gfx/wr/wrench/reftests/transforms/strange-w-ref.yaml", "gfx/wr/wrench/reftests/transforms/strange-w.yaml", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transforms/transform3d-matrix3d-005.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "68224b37ba35a78be80382f9c2c52fba23a2c5df", "parents": ["626e61fede41425cdde82038435fb53d97786032"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Hammond \u003cmhammond@skippinet.com.au\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539784 - ensure the master-password is unlocked before disconnecting from sync. r=eoger a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26870", "files": ["services/sync/modules/SyncDisconnect.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "37c5083230c5128f5c66ed88549e4471572d0e18", "parents": ["68224b37ba35a78be80382f9c2c52fba23a2c5df"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1541449 - storage.local API should fire onChanged event when falsey values are removed. r=mixedpuppy a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25949", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionStorageIDB.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_storage.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f56f6681da40857faa243da02f4d1fcb1dfaf2d", "parents": ["37c5083230c5128f5c66ed88549e4471572d0e18"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Perry Jiang \u003cperry@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539535 - Add a (temporary) null check in RemoteWorkerChild::CloseWorkerOnMainThread r=asuth a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26794", "files": ["dom/workers/remoteworkers/RemoteWorkerChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "afc3ac77b7750eae6581dae4cdf65b0678e8bea2", "parents": ["8f56f6681da40857faa243da02f4d1fcb1dfaf2d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530188 - Make nsChildView::GetEditorView() use eQueryContentState without flushing layout r=smaug a=pascalc\n\n`nsChildView::GetEditorView()` is called by `TextInputHandlerBase::GetWindowLevel()`\nwhich is called when Cocoa requests window level of focused widget.\n\nIt currently gets widget including focused element (e.g., it may be in a XUL\n`\u003cpanel\u003e`) with `eQueryTextContent` event.  However, it requires only the widget\n(i.e., when a XUL `\u003cpanel\u003e` has focused element, the widget for the panel).\nTherefore, it does not require to flush the layout.\n\nHowever, on macOS, `ContentEventHandler` always flushes layout even with\n`eQueryContentState` which does not require any layout information.  Whether\nit requires flushing layout or not is considered with\n`WidgetQueryContentEvent::mNeedsToFlushLayout` but this is set to false only\nwhen `IMEContentObserver` notifies widget (and IME) of focus set.  At this\ntime, only on macOS, IME caches the layout information, for example, the\ncharacter coordinates, but we don't have a way to update it.  This is the reason\nwhy we always flush layout on macOS.\n\nUnfortunately, when a menu popup frame is created, widget for the popup is\ncreated synchronously.  Then, Cocoa retrieves window level of the widget including\nfocused element.  But this is unsafe to flush the layout.  So, we need to stop\nflushing layout in this case.\n\nTherefore, this patch moves the `#ifdef` from `TextEvents.h` to\n`IMEContentObserver.cpp`, then, makes `nsChildView::GetEditorView()` use\n`eQueryContentState` which is the simplest query content event, and finally,\nsets `mNeedsToFlushLayout` to `false`.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D25912", "files": ["dom/events/IMEContentObserver.cpp", "widget/TextEvents.h", "widget/cocoa/nsChildView.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d9a704ef462353c6427f316faad23af8bd76832d", "parents": ["afc3ac77b7750eae6581dae4cdf65b0678e8bea2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1555199946, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "apavel@mozilla.com"}, "11082": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1542800 - Clear out any leftover updater tasks after the ClearTree task is run. r=botond a=pascalc\n\nThis patch ensures that once the ClearTree task is run on the updater\nthread, we throw away any other remaining tasks in the queue, as they\nwill never get run. (Note that the ClearTree task removes the APZUpdater\ninstance from the global map, and so it becomes \"unfindable\", meaning\nthe ProcessQueue will never run again on that instance).\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26541\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/public/APZUpdater.h", "gfx/layers/apz/src/APZUpdater.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e54cf3b64083747317a9675b587b1975dfa49607", "parents": ["d9a704ef462353c6427f316faad23af8bd76832d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1555201012, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kgupta@mozilla.com"}, "11083": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crele