 fully initialized. r=froydnj, a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D27231", "files": ["toolkit/crashreporter/breakpad-client/windows/crash_generation/crash_generation_server.cc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5e9f1cf0693663467059f729d897e2f23b4631e9", "parents": ["7ccaf23243177f7a103a6155f48f006ad0db545e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1555939292, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11124": {"changesets": [{"author": "Glenn Watson \u003cgithub@intuitionlibrary.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1543356 - Visual glitches on resizing the browser with WebRender. r=emilio a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D27978", "files": ["gfx/wr/webrender/src/renderer.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "50707a995cd56232e52b0e3453ec73c17e1339e6", "parents": ["5e9f1cf0693663467059f729d897e2f23b4631e9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jason Laster \u003cjlaster@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1543731 - When map scopes is disabled we should not compute mappings. r=loganfsmyth a=RyanVM", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/new/src/actions/pause/mapScopes.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b196e0c2e6a883a027266d6d11d647e9ef259599", "parents": ["50707a995cd56232e52b0e3453ec73c17e1339e6"], "tags": []}], "date": 1555941470, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "cbrindusan@mozilla.com"}, "11125": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Tung \u003cshes050117@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528690 - P1 - Mitigate the issue by checking the pointer before accessing it. r=asuth a=RyanVM\n\nThe real problem is because the connection was closed for some reason. This\npatch won't resolve the issue by only let the operation and the transaction fail\nto escape from the crash. Note that it also changing an assertion when the\ntransaction is either commiting or aborting. This is prevent the problem for\nclosing connection is worser than we expected.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D28148", "files": ["dom/indexedDB/ActorsParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ba1cb4f5a1cf8883cf7bd344cc4b8e16f411c621", "parents": ["b196e0c2e6a883a027266d6d11d647e9ef259599"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ian Moody \u003cmoz-ian@perix.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1470107 - Update Twemoji Mozilla to 0.4.0 (twemoji 11.4.0). r=jfkthame a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D27865", "files": ["browser/fonts/TwemojiMozilla.ttf", "layout/reftests/text/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "00567ac38963b491628cc9d70e131ffd4f67b029", "parents": ["ba1cb4f5a1cf8883cf7bd344cc4b8e16f411c621"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533071 - Enable OpenH264 plugin for win64-aarch64; r=jya a=RyanVM\n\nThis enables the OpenH264 plugin for win64-aarch64. It also disables hardware\ndecoding of OpenH264 on that platform due to Windows crashes when decoding\nOpenH264 streams.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D24917", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2e258ddb1483f5993821845a8713fe7b0aac5c7a", "parents": ["00567ac38963b491628cc9d70e131ffd4f67b029"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alexander Surkov \u003csurkov.alexander@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539414 - checkboxes are not redrawn on Win7 classic theme r=Gijs a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D27727", "files": ["toolkit/content/widgets/checkbox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9b8ad8b840ed4cc8545123c49a2cafb401e322d3", "parents": ["2e258ddb1483f5993821845a8713fe7b0aac5c7a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1540545 - Use consistent hit test options in AccessibleCaretManager. r=TYLin a=RyanVM\n\nIt's important to use the IgnoreRootScrollFrame for correct hit testing when\nzoomed in or out on Android. The hit test in DragCaretInternal() was missing\nthis flag.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D27636", "files": ["layout/base/AccessibleCaretManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ceb8833f34c3df62c7f4bf628ff769c1a638b240", "parents": ["9b8ad8b840ed4cc8545123c49a2cafb401e322d3"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_67_0b13_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_67_0b13_RELEASE", "FENNEC_67_0b13_BUILD1", "FENNEC_67_0b13_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_67_0b13_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_67_0b13_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1555951065, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "nbeleuzu@mozilla.com"}, "11126": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbe -\u003e 541f5874c2e9\nca -\u003e 4d12dc68052c\ncs -\u003e 58a84880350f\nes-AR -\u003e f4b4d2c1c034\nfi -\u003e 54b8058050d1\nid -\u003e 7f8b0a92a445\nkk -\u003e f5e36f24a066\nko -\u003e e2eb474fe493\nlij -\u003e 8f2318976e00\nlo -\u003e 2900c52dbffc\nlt -\u003e ddc2544b333a\nnn-NO -\u003e 66864d863abc\ntr -\u003e 86fd7114b4bc\nuk -\u003e 3c839c298eb9\nzh-CN -\u003e d8719694b398", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d001f7405c98a8042b87de0c1197eede05004bf3", "parents": ["ceb8833f34c3df62c7f4bf628ff769c1a638b240"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbe -\u003e 541f5874c2e9\nca -\u003e 7e9e66426168\ncs -\u003e 58a84880350f\nes-AR -\u003e 0fda80c4f839\nfi -\u003e 54b8058050d1\nfr -\u003e b67960a0e7e7\nid -\u003e 9b