r Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nde -\u003e cc371a18ce89", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a8888b75b12f4ca793beff29ab1a8325a0c2f1e1", "parents": ["5ea840bc95b62022581479d9313b91200f7e8e23"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nfr -\u003e acd54cc96f6d\nkm -\u003e 810e225db268\nzh-CN -\u003e 52086cbf3309", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "50c4f469bac44f9de651f740ebfbbbbc943ec056", "parents": ["a8888b75b12f4ca793beff29ab1a8325a0c2f1e1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1556805632, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11209": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1541489 - Don't turn on WR on 100% of qualified users at the start of release 67. r=jrmuizel a=pascalc\n\nWe'll use Normandy to deploy this gradually in 67.\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxPrefs.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7f749a11b5cf2fa0ffa9ed03084f9201d94f5d95", "parents": ["50c4f469bac44f9de651f740ebfbbbbc943ec056"], "tags": []}], "date": 1556813551, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kgupta@mozilla.com"}, "11210": {"changesets": [{"author": "Eden Chuang \u003cechuang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539208 - Propagate the result of mListener in InterceptedHttpChannel::OnStartRequest and ::OnStopRequest r=perry,ttung,kershaw a=pascalc\n\n1. Propagate the mListener's result in InterceptedHttpChannel::OnStartRequest()\n   and ::OnStopRequest().\n\n2. remove unnecessary assertion in FetchDriver::OnStartRequest().\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D28477", "files": ["dom/fetch/FetchDriver.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/InterceptedHttpChannel.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "224c70ce5efff2b014309e448dcc43a759e43441", "parents": ["7f749a11b5cf2fa0ffa9ed03084f9201d94f5d95"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriele Svelto \u003cgsvelto@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1545593 - Enable tab unloading in low-memory scenarios unconditionally r=mconley a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D28146", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "11d3470f983ebc901d3fb15fb0cc779951f4221b", "parents": ["224c70ce5efff2b014309e448dcc43a759e43441"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529892 - Limit the area of a fixed-position element that's painted to the displayport. r=kats a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D28775", "files": ["layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ce52ad329dab177d22c3cfdad819e54261d9d343", "parents": ["11d3470f983ebc901d3fb15fb0cc779951f4221b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1556814303, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "cbrindusan@mozilla.com"}, "11211": {"changesets": [{"author": "Perry Jiang \u003cperry@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1535699 - Propagate redirect mode across cross-process redirects. r=asuth a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D29719", "files": ["dom/ipc/ContentChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/ContentChild.h", "dom/ipc/PContent.ipdl", "dom/serviceworkers/test/browser.ini", "dom/serviceworkers/test/browser_navigation_process_swap.js", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelParentListener.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "89ab6b801db05cfcbdb94e9376d3db952ada4011", "parents": ["ce52ad329dab177d22c3cfdad819e54261d9d343"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nika Layzell \u003cnika@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539959 - Ensure origin process is subscribed when attaching remote BC, r=farre a=pascalc\n\nWe were incorrectly not performing an EnsureSubscribed for the origin\nprocess which a BrowsingContext came from. Normally this would mean that\nthe BrowsingContext could die in the parent process before the\nWindowGlobalParent listener arrived, but that didn't generally happen\ndue to the low likelihood of a CC occuring between the two messages.\n\nIt's likely that this crash was caused by people on lower-end hardware\ntriggering a print. This would be a longer-running operation in the\ncontent process between the first and second message than usual. On\nsystems with memory pressure, there would be a higher chance of a CC\noccuring between the messages, which would then cause this crash.\n\nThis patch correctly connects the origin ContentParent to the\nBrowsingContextGroup, which will prevent the CC from destroying our\nobjects.\n\nIn the future, it may be desirable to ensure that this doesn't happen\nmore reliably by using a ContentParent-local table for looking up\nBrowsingContext IDs sent over IPC. This would prevent our current\ndependency on the weak pointer behaviour of the current global ID cache.\n\nUnfortunately, this patch adds no tests, and I'm not aware of a good way\nto test this edge case to confirm it has been fixed. I believe that this\npatch should fix the issue I mention, however.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D29563", "files": ["docshell/base/BrowsingContext.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e9cc7e9d9c734497f3e9c226cbda678871ebbe06", "parents": ["89ab6b801db05cfcbdb94e9376d3db952ada4011"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522817 - Expose possibly-gray global object before passing it into the JS API in Document::AdoptNode r=bzbarsky a=pascalc\n\nCurrently Document::AdoptNode gets the JS global object, but in a way that does not expose it first, so it's possible for this to pass a gray object in here.  From the comments it seems like this doesn't matter, but it does break our invariant that no gray objects are passed into the API.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D29210", "files": ["dom/base/Document.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cdf167f4186a12d4e5cf34655dfd201da159f0cd", "parents": ["e9cc7e9d9c734497f3e9c226cbda678871ebbe06"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_67_0b16_BUILD1", "FENNEC_67_0b16_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_67_0b16_BUILD1"]}], "date": 1556837311, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "rgurzau@mozilla.com"}, "11212": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522817 - Always expose returned target object of wrapper r=sfink a=pascalc\n\nThe comment here talks about unmarking wrapper targets in case we're in incremental GC, but it does it conditially based on the color of the wrapper.  We can't depend on that because a wrapper marked gray may eventually be marked black.  Also, I don't think we should be touching gray wrappers anyway.  Let's just always expose here.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D29211", "files": ["js/src/proxy/Wrapper.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bb9c48a4e71aa927d148b7e91dfda6417c507c13", "parents": ["cdf167f4186a12d4e5cf34655dfd201da159f0cd"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_67_0b16_BUILD2", "DEVEDITION_67_0b16_RELEASE", "FENNEC_67_0b16_BUILD2", "FENNEC_67_0b16_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_67_0b16_BUILD2", "FIREFOX_67_0b16_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1556839319, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "rgurzau@mozilla.com"}, "11213": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging cdf167f4186a12d4e5cf34655dfd201da159f0cd with FENNEC_67_0b16_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3f79f8d0572e48d5ffd89cf3088a96bca173469d", "parents": ["bb9c48a4e71aa927d148b7e91dfda6417c507c13"], "tags": []}], "date": 1556839610, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11214": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging cdf167f4186a12d4e5cf34655dfd201da159f0cd with DEVEDITION_67_0b16_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c8bf3d95ec162c362ff29a758668bce1715d1a7e", "parents": ["3f79f8d0572e48d5ffd89cf3088a96bca173469d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1556839933, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11215": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging bb9c48a4e71aa927d148b7e91dfda6417c507c13 with FENNEC_67_0b16_BUILD2 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8b7e102474207e8c7e390e3871f05a9717b68930", "parents": ["c8bf3d95ec162c362ff29a758668bce1715d1a7e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1556840306, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11216": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging cdf167f4186a12d4e5cf34655dfd201da159f0cd with FIREFOX_67_0b16_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c15fd18c005e85f9b9888d6cbd6aba086ed16e67", "parents": ["8b7e102474207e8c7e390e3871f05a9717b68930"], "tags": []}], "date": 1556840489, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11217": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging bb9c48a4e71a